| Sr. No. | Test Plan Point               | Answer                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                |
| ------: | ----------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
|       1 | **Test Plan Identifier**      | OARS_TEST_PLAN_v1.0 — Online Admission & Registration System (OARS) — Functional, Integration, System, Security & Performance Testing                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 |
|       2 | **References**                | 1. OARS Functional Specification v1.2<br>2. OARS UI/UX Mockups (Figma) v1.0<br>3. OARS Data Model & API Spec v0.9<br>4. IEEE 829 Test Documentation Guidelines<br>5. Payment Gateway Integration Guide (PG_VENDOR_X)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  |
|       3 | **Introduction**              | **Purpose:** Validate correctness, reliability, security, and usability of OARS which allows global applicants to create accounts, fill applications, upload documents, check admission status, receive decisions, and pay fees.<br>**Scope:** End-to-end admission workflow (signup → login → form fill → uploads → status check → decision → payment). Out-of-scope: third-party background-check integrations, offline/manual admission flows. <br>**Objectives:** Ensure correctness of business rules, data validation, document handling, notifications, secure payments, scalability for expected concurrent applicants, and compliance with accessibility basics.                                                                                                                                             |
|       4 | **Features to be Tested**     | 1. User registration (create username, email verification).<br>2. Login/logout and session management.<br>3. Application form (field validation, progressive save, edit).<br>4. File upload & attachment (supported types, max size, multiple docs).<br>5. Application submission & status tracking (Submitted, Under Review, Accepted, Rejected, On Hold).<br>6. Decision handling & notifications (email/SMS).<br>7. Payment processing (credit/debit card and net-banking).<br>8. Security checks (auth, input validation, session expiration, SQL/XSS).<br>9. Cross-browser compatibility and responsive UI.<br>10. Performance under concurrent users (basic load).                                                                                                                                              |
|       5 | **Approach**                  | **Test levels:** Unit (dev), Integration (APIs), System (end-to-end), Acceptance (UX & functional).<br>**Testing types:** Functional, Negative, Security (input sanitization), Usability, Compatibility (Chrome/Firefox/Edge; Desktop/Mobile), Performance (smoke load), Regression. <br>**Test techniques:** Manual exploratory + scripted automated tests using Selenium + PyTest for critical flows (registration, login, upload, payment sandbox). Use mock payment gateway/sandbox for automated payment tests. Use test data sets (valid/invalid) and test accounts. <br>**Entry Criteria:** Dev build deployed to test environment; DB seeded with test accounts; payment sandbox credentials available. <br>**Exit Criteria:** All critical test cases passed; no P1/P2 defects open; regression tests green. |
|       6 | **Environmental Needs**       | **Hardware/OS:** Windows 10/11, Ubuntu 22.04, macOS (optional).<br>**Browsers:** Chrome (latest), Firefox (latest), Edge (latest), Mobile Chrome (Android emulator).<br>**Test servers:** QA application URL, Test DB, Test SMTP, Payment gateway sandbox, File storage (test S3 or local).<br>**Tools:** Selenium + PyTest, Postman (API checks), JMeter (basic load), Browser DevTools, Git. <br>**Test Data:** Seeded users, sample documents (pdf, jpg, png), card test numbers for sandbox.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |
|       7 | **Staffing & Training Needs** | **Staff:** 1 Test Lead, 2 Functional Testers, 1 Automation Tester, 1 Performance Tester (part-time), 1 Security Tester (part-time).<br>**Training:** Intro to payment sandbox usage, test environment access instructions, automation framework onboarding (Selenium+PyTest), data privacy handling for test documents.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
|       8 | **Responsibilities**          | **Test Lead:** Plan & report progress, manage risks.<br>**Functional Testers:** Execute manual test cases, report defects.<br>**Automation Tester:** Implement automated suites for smoke/regression flows.<br>**Dev Team:** Fix defects, provide build deployments.<br>**Ops:** Maintain QA environment, rollback/restore DB as needed.<br>**Business Owner:** Sign off acceptance criteria.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         |
|       9 | **Schedule**                  | *High-level (example timeline):*<br>- Test Plan review & approval: Day 1–2<br>- Environment setup & test data seeding: Day 2–4<br>- Smoke & Sanity tests (automated): Day 5–6<br>- Functional testing (manual): Day 7–14<br>- Automation of regressions: Day 10–16 (parallel)<br>- Security & performance quick checks: Day 12–16<br>- UAT & sign-off: Day 17–18<br>*(Adjust to your exam/project dates; this is a sample 3-week plan scaled down as needed.)*                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        |
